<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <body>
        <h2>JavaScript Array</h2>
        <h2>join() and pop()</h2>
        <p>The join() method join the array to the string and pop() removes it from an array</P>

            <p id="myjoin"></p>
            <p id="myfirstpop"></p>
            <p id="mysecondpop"></p>
            <script>
                var fruits = ["Banana", "Apple", "Orange","Mango"];
                 document.getElementById("myjoin").innerHTML = fruits.join(" * ");
                 document.getElementById("myfirstpop").innerHTML = fruits;
                 fruits.pop();
                 document.getElementById("mysecondpop").innerHTML =fruits;
            
            </script>
    </body>
</html>